Dijkstras Algorithm

There is a group of nodes (ex 9)
labeled 1 through 9
nodes are connected through lines in between them, they are not all connected to each other, only some to others.
each path has a weight.
there is a node where you start. (in some cases you can also have a destination node)
priority queue is needed (heap.c and heap.h are given to us in his code).
start node has weight 0, as you are already there.
put nodes into queue with their cost, start is 0, others are infinity.
queue also has a predecesor for previous node, 0 does NOT have a predecesor.
look at neighboring nodes, see costs and update costs based on the weight from current point to neighboring point. 
update pred on neighboring nodes to current node.
node one is "marked off" as it already has its costs and predecesors calculated.
repeat this with the lowest costing node until all nodes have cost and pred values.
if a shorter path is found during the algo, replace cost with lower cost.
once algo is finished, all you have to do is choose a node you want to travel to, and follow the predecessors all the way to the start node.

